        "## 21.9 Interactive module: gated memory in LSTM and GRU\n",
        "\n",
        "The next module gives a simplified gate-level view. The gates are fixed sliders rather than learned functions of $x_t$ and $h_{t-1}$. This is not a full trained LSTM or GRU; it is a controlled visualization of what the gates do.\n",
        "\n",
        "For the LSTM view, the scalar equations are\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "c_t=f c_{t-1}+i\\widetilde c_t,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "h_t=o\\tanh(c_t).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For the GRU view, the scalar equations are\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widetilde h_t=\\tanh(gx_t+r h_{t-1}),\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "h_t=(1-z)h_{t-1}+z\\widetilde h_t.\n",
        "$$\n",
